# CustomArc Web — Frontend Agent Guide

> Apply on any change under `apps/web/`. Spec: `docs/phase-1/spec.md`. Brand: Air Blush.

## Stack

Next.js App Router · React 19 · **Tailwind CSS v4** · **shadcn/ui + Base UI** · Lucide

## Styling doctrine (non-negotiable)

1. **Tailwind first** — layout, spacing, typography, color, states via utilities.
2. **Theme tokens live in root** — `apps/web/app/globals.css` `:root` + `@theme inline`.
3. **Do not add new component CSS classes** to `globals.css`.
4. **Custom CSS only when Tailwind cannot** (e.g. multi-layer body gradient). Comment why.
5. Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes.

## Brand tokens → Tailwind

| Token | Utility examples |
|---|---|
| `--bg` / `--background` | `bg-bg` `bg-background` |
| `--fg` / `--foreground` | `text-fg` `text-foreground` |
| `--fg-muted` / `--muted-foreground` | `text-fg-muted` `text-muted-foreground` |
| `--primary` / `--accent` (`#c45c6a`) | `bg-primary` `text-primary` `border-primary` |
| `--primary-foreground` | `text-primary-foreground` |
| `--border` | `border-border` |
| `--card` | `bg-card` |
| `--maxw` | `max-w-content` |
| `--header-h` | `pt-[var(--header-h)]` / `--spacing-header` |

Never hard-code `#c45c6a` in components — use `primary` / token utilities.

## Components

```
apps/web/components/
  ui/     ← shadcn primitives only (Button, Dialog, Input, …)
  *.tsx   ← product UI (header, auth-modal) — compose ui/* + Tailwind
```

- Add: `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <name> -c apps/web`
- Import: `@/components/ui/<name>`
- No business logic inside `ui/`

## Practices

- DRY / KISS / YAGNI — short, reusable pieces
- Prefer Server Components; `'use client'` only for interactivity
- A11y: ≥44px targets, `focus-visible`, labels, Escape/dialogs
- Prefer shadcn + Tailwind over reinventing Dialog/Tabs/Button
- Match Air Blush: soft blush bg, accent rose, sharp small radius
- **Routing:** use `next/link` (`Link`) for internal navigation — never raw `<a href>`
- **Images:** use `next/image` (`Image`) for photos/assets — never raw `<img>` (icons via Lucide are fine)

## Anti-patterns

- New `.hero` / `.card` / `.btn` CSS in `globals.css`
- Inline `style={{ color: '#c45c6a' }}` for theme colors
- Installing a second UI kit (MUI, Chakra, …)
- Hand-rolled modal when `Dialog` exists
- Resetting shadcn theme to neutral gray defaults
- Raw `<a>` / `<img>` for in-app routes or product media
